<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Occipital marking Y-shaped. Flagellar verticils 3 times longer than corresponding segment. Postgena with short narrow stripe near inner margin of eyes. Prescutum with one broad, dark-brown mid-longitudinal stripe. Wing 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="stigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigma">stigma</taxonomicName>
pale brown with yellowish brown margin; Sc1 apically reaching 3/5 of Rs. Abdominal dorsum with one dark-brown mid-longitudinal stripe. Posterior margin of tergite 9 with two finger-like sclerotized protrusions. Gonostylus with blunt apex and swollen base. Paramere reniform, apex ended at 2/5 of aedeagus. Aedeagus with strong ventral mid-protrusion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Male</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">n</emphasis>
= 2): body length 9-10.5 mm, wing length 10-11 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Head</emphasis>
mostly yellow (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">11</figureCitation>
). Vertex dull yellow. Occiput dull yellow, covered with black setulae. Occipital marking dark brown, but pale brown at posterior part, Y-shaped, with anterior marking linked with inner margin of eyes. Head with black setulae. Antenna 14-segmented; scape dark brown, pedicel yellowish brown, flagellomeres yellowish brown; flagellar verticils black, three times longer than corresponding segment. Nasus 1/2 as long as rostrum. Rostrum and nasus brown to dark brown. Labella pale yellow, with black setulae and inner margin with brown. Postgena light yellow with short narrow stripe near inner margin of eyes. Palpi dark brown with black setulae.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" start="Figures 10–12" startId="F4">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Figures 10-12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ren &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limonia medexocha" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medexocha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Limonia medexocha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., male 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">10</emphasis>
male habitus, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">11</emphasis>
head and thorax, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">12</emphasis>
right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Thorax</emphasis>
mostly yellow (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">11</figureCitation>
). Cervical sclerite pale brown with black outer margin. Pronotum dull yellow with dull brown median stripe. Prescutum with one broad, dark-brown mid-longitudinal stripe and black setulae at lateral margin. Scutum dark brown with black setulae around outer margin. Scutellum dark brown with tapered yellow median stripe. Mediotergite dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">11</figureCitation>
). Mesopleura entirely light yellow except katepisternum with dark brown margin at antero-lateral corner and subspiracular sclerite dull yellow; center of episternum with eight black setulae. Legs with coxae and trochanters yellow; femora yellowish brown with dark-brown terminal ring; tibiae yellowish brown, with dull brown subapical ring; tarsi reddish brown to dark brown. Setulae on legs black. Wing hyaline, pale brown; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="stigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigma">stigma</taxonomicName>
pale brown with yellowish brown margin; Sc1 apically reaching 3/5 of Rs; while Sc2 apically reaching 3/4 of Rs; basal deflection of CuA1 far before branching point of M. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">12</figureCitation>
). Halter with dull-brown stem and pale-brown to dark-brown knob (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Abdomen</emphasis>
mainly light yellow (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">10</figureCitation>
). Dorsum with one dark-brown mid-longitudinal stripe. Abdominal segments 7-9 entirely dark brown; hypopygium mostly dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–9" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 9. Limonia macrostigma, female 8 cercus and hypogynial valves, lateral view 9 cercus and hypogynial valves, ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures8-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456134" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">9</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">12</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of tergite 9 with two finger-like, sclerotized protrusions that constrict at base and project outward at apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–9" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 9. Limonia macrostigma, female 8 cercus and hypogynial valves, lateral view 9 cercus and hypogynial valves, ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures8-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456134" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">9</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite wide at base and narrow at apex, longer than wide. Gonostylus with blunt apex and swollen basal protrusion that is strongly outward and hairy (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–9" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 9. Limonia macrostigma, female 8 cercus and hypogynial valves, lateral view 9 cercus and hypogynial valves, ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures8-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456134" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">9</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 10 male habitus, lateral view 11 head and thorax, dorsal view 12 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456135" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">11</figureCitation>
). Paramere reniform with small apical protrusion and rod-shaped; apex ended at 2/5 of aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–16" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 13 - 16. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 13 hypopygium, dorsal view 14 hypopygium, ventral view 15 hypopygium, lateral view 16 aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures13-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456136" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">13-16</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus complex; mid-ventral margin with strong protrusion which is long and rectangular in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–16" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 13 - 16. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 13 hypopygium, dorsal view 14 hypopygium, ventral view 15 hypopygium, lateral view 16 aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures13-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456136" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">15</figureCitation>
); outer margin serrated; apex with small notch; spherical protrusion located mid-ventrally at base (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–16" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 13 - 16. Limonia medexocha sp. nov., male 13 hypopygium, dorsal view 14 hypopygium, ventral view 15 hypopygium, lateral view 16 aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures13-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456136" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">13-16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
